<div class="os-selector">
    <ul>
        <li class="android">
            <a onclick="setActiveOS('android')">
                <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-android" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                <span>Android</span>
            </a>
        </li>
        <li class="linux">
            <a onclick="setActiveOS('linux')">
                <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-linux" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                <span>Linux</span>
            </a>
        </li>
        <li class="macos">
            <a onclick="setActiveOS('macos')">
                <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-apple" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                <span>macOS</span>
            </a>
        </li>
        <li class="windows">
            <a onclick="setActiveOS('windows')">
                <span class="icon is-small"><i class="fab fa-windows" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                <span>Windows</span>
            </a>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="os-body">
    <div class="android is-hidden">
        <div class="buttons is-centered">
            <a class="button is-link" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=tech.relaycorp.gateway">
                <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
                Install from the Play Store
            </a>
        </div>

        <p>
            You can use <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=tech.relaycorp.ping">Awala Ping</a> to
            test Awala with and without access to the Internet.
        </p>

        <p>
            We're also planning to publish Awala on <a href="https://www.f-droid.org/">F-Droid</a> to facilitate
            offline distribution. Stay tuned!
        </p>

        <p>
            If you're a technical person looking for the source code, you'll find it on
            <a href="{{ android.githubRepoURL }}"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> {{ android.githubRepoName }}</a>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="linux">
        <div class="buttons is-centered">
            <a class="button is-link" href="{{ desktop.linuxDownloadURL }}">
                <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
                Download Awala for Linux
            </a>
        </div>

        <p>
            Awala is currently distributed as an <a href="https://appimage.org/">AppImage</a>, which
            means you have to edit the permissions of the file to make it executable
            before you use it for the first time. We're also planning to publish Awala on
            <a href="https://snapcraft.io/">Snapcraft</a> — stay tuned!
        </p>

        <p>
            You can use <a href="{{ desktop.pingURL }}">Awala Ping</a> to
            test Awala with and without access to the Internet.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you're a technical person looking for the source code, you'll find it on
            <a href="{{ desktop.githubRepoURL }}"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> {{ desktop.githubRepoName }}</a>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="macos">
        <div class="buttons is-centered">
            <a class="button is-link" href="{{ desktop.macosDownloadURL }}">
                <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
                Download Awala for macOS
            </a>
        </div>

        <p>
            macOS support is currently experimental and its installer is not signed by Relaycorp yet.
            We're also planning to publish Awala on the App Store eventually — stay tuned!
        </p>

        <p>
            You can use <a href="{{ desktop.pingURL }}">Awala Ping</a> to
            test Awala with and without access to the Internet.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you're a technical person looking for the source code, you'll find it on
            <a href="{{ desktop.githubRepoURL }}"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> {{ desktop.githubRepoName }}</a>.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="windows">
        <div class="buttons is-centered">
            <a class="button is-link" href="{{ desktop.windowsDownloadURL }}">
                <i class="fas fa-download"></i>
                Download Awala for Windows
            </a>
        </div>

        <p>
            Windows should show <em>Relaycorp, Inc.</em> as the publisher of the installer. Do not
            proceed with the installation if a different publisher is shown. We're also planning to publish Awala on
            the Microsoft Store eventually — stay tuned!
        </p>

        <p>
            You can use <a href="{{ desktop.pingURL }}">Awala Ping</a> to
            test Awala with and without access to the Internet.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you're a technical person looking for the source code, you'll find it on
            <a href="{{ desktop.githubRepoURL }}"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> {{ desktop.githubRepoName }}</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
